title: The Wombats to play Falls Festival
text:
New names to play Lorne Falls Festival exclusively by: What are these? The Dune Rats will perform at Lorne’s Falls Festival. Source: Supplied 
THE Falls Festival line-up has been fattened up with 28 new acts added exclusively to the Lorne leg. 
Topping the list of newcomers set to perform at the festival’s birth place was The Wombats, Lurch and Chief, Melbourne Ska Orchestra, Dune Rats and the Bennies. 
Announced this morning, the list also included Ngaiire, The Lords, The Babe Rainbow, Ainslee Wills, Peter Bibby and Dewbury plus a handful of bands, DJs and soloists. 
While the UK trio responsible for Your Body is a Weapon was the only international add on, other new Australian acts include soloist Harts, DJ Yoda, City Calm Down, Banoffee and Holy Holy. 
The names will join the likes of Courtney Barnett, Foals, Disclosure and Bloc Party already billed for the New Year’s Eve festival.
